Dear Families:

We hope all is well with you during these difficult times.

This afternoon Gov. Lamont announced that schools will remain closed through the remainder of the school year. To ensure that Capital Prep‚Äôs scholars and families continue to receive academic, social, and emotional support, our distance learning will continue through our scheduled last day of June 19th.

Communications will continue to be updated via ParentSquare, the Parent Portal on our website, and our Social Media.

Stay safe,

Dr. Ayanna Carter and Ronald Hawkins
Capital Prep Harbor

Be a for-profit company
Have between 2 and 50 employees
Have been in business for over a year
Have experienced challenges from COVID-19
Be in or near a location where Facebook operates

Dairy foods are recommended as part of healthy eating patterns in part because of the important nutrients they deliver including calcium, phosphorus, and vitamins like A, D and B12, and protein. To help provide this nutrient-rich food to people in a sustainable and responsible way, dairy farmers partner with experts in their community such as veterinarians, nutritionists, and technologists. The Undeniably Dairy Virtual Field Trip takes students behind-the-scenes to show them key ways farmers and the dairy community bring dairy foods from the dairy farm-to-table while contributing to sustainable food systems that are good for the land, animals, people, and the planet. Join Principal Hawkins as we find out about the advances on today‚Äôs farms.

Topic: UndeniablyDairy Virtual Field Trip
Time: Apr 11, 2020 01:00 PM Eastern Time (US and Canada)

Join Zoom Meeting
https://zoom.us/j/6203942509?pwd=bG5kd1dlcFEydTdiZUMxMmprWDB5dz09

Meeting ID: 620 394 2509

post_text:
Dear Families:

As previously communicated, and following the announcement today, we are following the closure of the Bridgeport Public School District. With that, we will close our Harbor Upper and Lower campuses tomorrow, March 13, and enter next week with our regularly scheduled Spring Break through Friday. Bridgeport Public Schools are closed for the week as well, and we will update you over the break if our closure will be extended into the week of March 23.

Spring Break work is posted on the website under the Parent Portal.

If you have any questions regarding our operations during this time, please use the email info@wearecapitalprep.org. This email will be regularly monitored, and will be responded to within 3 hours from 8am-6pm, or within 24 hours if after 6pm.

Best Regards,

Capital Prep Harbor Administration
